programme.title: Messy Goes To Okido

All the girls except Strawberry begin jumping to conclusions about what could be causing the problem. programme.title: Thomas And Friends

programme.title: Grisu

Fortunately, he finds an original solution by creating a kind of suspended train, hanging on the streetlamps (like a car assembly line).

Will Little Nutbrown Hare manage to stay inside, or will he be tempted out as well?

programme.title: Guess How Much I Love You

programme.title: Bob the Builder

programme.title: Leo the Wildlife Ranger

programme.desc: Bing has a great time choosing the perfect present for Sula in Padgets shop. Its a wand and is sparkly and flashy and spinny and Bing knows that she will love it. Bing is thrilled until it is time to hand the present over.

programme.title: Bing Bunny
programme.desc: Bing wants to try Coco’s Hula Hoop. It’s harder than it looks but he finds lots of other hoopy games as he tries. Just as Bing almost gets it right he gets carried away with spinning, trips over and breaks the hoop. Coco is upset that she can’t hula anymore until Bing and Charlie remind her of all the other games they can still do with the bent hoop.

programme.title: Oswald
programme.desc: Oswald and Daisy are making sticky honey buns, but Daisy doesn’t follow the recipe properly and they end up getting stuck to the dough -- and each other! -- instead. They ask Henry for help, and he ends up getting stuck as well. The three then head through Big City, and everyone they meet somehow ends up getting stuck, too. But when they think that it couldn’t get much worse, it starts to rain! Oswald suddenly realises that they can become unstuck by standing in the rain and sure enough the sticky dough gets washed away.

programme.title: Oswald
programme.desc: Pongo the Friendly Dragon is sad because he doesn’t have anyone his size to play with and can’t enjoy activities like riding on the seesaw. Feeling sorry for his friend, Oswald finds the perfect match for Pongo - Laverne the White Elephant - but Pongo is too shy to say hello to her. Oswald devises ways to get them together, but the clumsy Pongo keeps ruining his efforts. Finally Oswald manoeuvres both Pongo and Laverne into the basket of a hot-air balloon and sets them adrift, and they float off together, friends at last.

programme.title: Bob the Builder
programme.desc: At the new Skyscraper Bob and the team find that Mayor Madison wants the elevator finished so she can have her photo taken at the top. Scoop wants to see the ‘whole of Spring City’ too. He rolls into Tiny’s cage but on the way up realises that he’s not so keen after all and in panic rolls onto high up floor girders of the unfinished skyscraper. Bob embarks on a daring rescue. Realising that Bob is taking a risk to help him Scoop manages to control himself and roll back into the cage. From now on, he’d rather keep his wheels firmly on the ground!

programme.title: Bob the Builder
programme.desc: When Bob and the team arrive at Chef Tattie’s fun new Milk Shake Bar, Scoop sees Chef Tattie experimenting with ingredients for his milk shakes and gets inspired. Scoop decides that he will do the same when he he helps Two-Tonne mix up the concrete for the Car Park. But the next morning, it’s soon clear that Scoop’s concrete isn’t dry. Scoop has to scrape it all off so they can start again. But Bob thinks there might be something to Scoop’s idea to make a fun car park after all and gives him some crazy but ‘proper’ materials to mix up in Dizzy.

programme.title: Guess How Much I Love You
programme.desc: Little Nutbrown Hare awakes to find the leaves changing colour and falling off the trees, the flowers dropping off the bushes and the tadpoles turning into frogs. Autumn is here and it’s time for change! Little Nutbrown Hare misses the joys of the Summer meadow. Will he discover that Autumn has it’s own delights?

programme.title: Guess How Much I Love You
programme.desc: The cool Autumn breeze isn’t enough to deter Little Nutbrown Hare and Little Field Mouse from going out to find what special experiences the day might bring. However, with the weather and wind constantly changing, it’s very hard for the friends continue playing any one game. Will the strange weather spoil their fun, or will it bring them a special experience after all?

programme.title: Guess How Much I Love You
programme.desc: Among the newly fallen Autumn leaves Little Nutbrown Hare finds a very peculiar little, hairy, green… ‘something’. Intrigued by what it might be Little Nutbrown Hare asks all his friends, but they all have different answers! It is certainly a very useful ‘something’, great for back scratching and games but it takes Little Grey Squirrel to solve the mystery.

programme.title: Learning Time With Timmy
programme.desc: It’s snack time and everyone has a cookie. Timmy wants to share his cookie with his friends. Help Timmy cut the cookie and count.

programme.title: Hurray for Huckle!
programme.desc: Forgetful Mayor Fox has misplaced the giant key to the city that hes supposed to be presenting to a visiting astronaut. Huckle and his pals try to figure out where he set it down. They learn that Mayor Fox did one thing while touring a candy factory that required both his hands - stirring a huge pot of candy goo. Not far away they find a big chocolate-covered key./When Busytown residents are baffled by mysterious door knocking, Huckle and gang discover who it is.

programme.title: Messy Goes To Okido
programme.desc: In the real world, Messy has just woken up and is looking for his sock breakfast, but it is under his toy box and he can’t reach, or move it… He needs to know how to move heavy things, and the best place to find out the answer is Okido! When he arrives Zoe and Felix are also trying to move a heavy box! They need to go to the recycling centre today. So they all go to Zam and Zim to find out the best way to do it. Zim, Zam and Zoom are sunbathing and enjoying Zam’s latest invention when the three arrive.

programme.title: Messy Goes To Okido
programme.desc: In the real world Messy walks into the bathroom and is horrified to find it clean! It’s not right for a Messy Monster at all. “Why do you have to clean things anyway?” He asks himself. And he goes to Okido to find out! When he arrives Felix and Zoe are at the top of their treehouse and there is a noisy racket going on! They don’t know what it could be so they skidoodle to go and have a look. When they arrive in the centre of Okido there are funny little things making lots of noise hurtling around the streets and sending the Okidinians into chaos!

programme.title: Strawberry Shortcakes Berry Bitty Adventures
programme.desc: The girls decide to each bake Berrykin Bloom the perfect cupcake, to be presented at a ceremony honoring him for his achievements in Berryculture. Their efforts get comically out of control as they begin competing with each other to create the biggest and best cupcake ever!

programme.title: Harry And His Bucket Full Of Dinosaurs
programme.desc: Harry and the dinos discover that theres a new dinosaur in the house, and it belongs to Nana.

programme.title: Harry And His Bucket Full Of Dinosaurs
programme.desc: Harry wants to sleep out in his new tent in the garden so that he can practice his scout skills.

programme.title: Leo the Wildlife Ranger
programme.desc: Zari was talking to her mom on her phone as she walks down a lonely street lined with a lampposts. As she stops under a lamppost and the light begins to flicker, she slowly looks upwards to see a monster hanging from a lamppost. She skates away in fear, and remember her phone was there. She returns to the area and notice the so-called monster looks like a bat. Back in the garden, Leo is practicing with his jetpack maneuvering skill by performing spiral pattern and zig zag. He talks to Katie who is by her computer. After almost crashing into Hero the dog, Leo crash lands on the ground. Katie jokes on his skill before Leo receives a call from Zari. Zari informs them of the monster she met, which they later to learn it is a Greater Flying Fox. After agreeing to help Zari out, the Junior Rangers travels to her location. They meet up with Zari under the lamppost, where she show them of the animal. Hero tries barking at the animal but it ignores him. Katie has an idea and pulled her tablet to guide the flying fox away. Leo takes Katies tablet and fly with his jetpack to guide the Flying fox. As they were travelling, Katie notices Leos Jetpack is malfunctioning, causing Leo to have issues with flying and he crash land uncontrollably into a bush. They check up on him and Leo is okay.

programme.title: Thomas And Friends
programme.desc: The whole island is celebrating Christmas and there are decorations everywhere, but it doesn’t look very Christmassy at the scrap yard. Percy starts to worry that Reg is missing out and he tries to find something to take to Reg to cheer him up. But the only thing Reg seems happy about is scrap. Percy discovers that Reg is celebrating Christmas his own way and has been making his own decorations from scrap.

programme.title: Thomas And Friends
programme.desc: One day while repairing an embankment, Marion strikes something hard and insists it must be the mast of a Viking Ship. It looks like a water pipe to Thomas but Marion is adamant that it isn’t. But the next day Thomas notices flooding near the bank and then there is a landslip and Marion has to admit her mistake and help prevent an accident.

programme.title: Grisu
programme.desc: After an expedition to the Jungle, Doctor Natureza finds out that a little monkey, Simmy, hid in her plane and followed her to Dragontown. Grisu has to help Natureza to bring the monkey back and reintroduce into the wild. But Simmy doesn’t seem to be in a rush to return to wildlife and, being quite cheeky and lively, it gives Grisu a hard time. Eventually, the little dragon finds out that the monkey needs to make peace with its brother Sammy, and after that the two apes return to their home in the Jungle together

programme.title: Grisu
programme.desc: Olivia and Sandro are preparing orienteering training for the crew. David and Steffan are to meet them but have been called to another mission. But they can’t let Olivia and Steffan know as their walkie-talkie isn’t working. Grisu volunteers to deliver the message with Stella’s help and following the map Olivia has prepared. But they must get to the firefighters before the enter the cave at the end of the trail. Grisu and Stella have to work without a compass after Fume breaks it; but using traditional navigation methods and with an ingenious invention from Grisu when all seems lost, the manage to deliver their message just in time.

programme.title: Guess How Much I Love You
programme.desc: On a cold but sunny morning in the middle of Winter, Little Nutbrown Hare discovers his friends ice-skating on the frozen pond. He decides to give it a try but slips, slops and slides all over the ice. Will he persevere for long enough to be able to perfect his own unique style, or will he be put off by the natural skill of his friends?

programme.title: Richard Strauss et ses heroïnes
programme.desc: Divorce! After six years of marriage the choleric and chronically jealous Pauline, daughter of a general, has had enough of Richard Strauss. Pauline always knew it: her husband who at 36 is celebrated as the most important living German composer across the globe is cheating on her. His congeniality and moral uprightness is just a mask! Are his inspirations for the erotic escapades which are the basis of several of his tone poems and songs based on the love affairs of the artist? The film Richard Strauss and his Heroines goes on an exciting journey discovering the women in Strauss’ life. At the focus is primarily his relationship with Pauline, to whom he was married for over 55 years up to his death. Until today she applies as a harridan who often embarrassed her husband in public. It hereby falls under the table that Strauss at the beginning and the end of his relationship composed his finest songs for the trained singer who gave up her career for him and covered his back for the rest of his life. What was it that made the broken old man, who experienced the most varied of epochs in German history, from the Empire to the Nazi dictatorship to the post-war period, write in 1948 in his final song (“At Sunset”) one of the most moving declarations of love in the history of music: “We have through sorrow and joy gone hand in hand”? We visit Strauss last surviving grandchild in Garmisch and we meet the great Strauss singers Brigitte Fassbaender, Renee Fleming, Dame Gwyneth Jones and Christa Ludwig, who report on their famous Strauss roles. With the conductor Franz Welser-Most we research the secret of Strauss’ instrumentation genius.Subtitles available for this program with your remote control

programme.title: La vie que jaime - Le pianiste Menahem Pressler
programme.desc: The music world has known Menahem Pressler for more than half a century and mainly for his work with the famous Beaux Arts Trio. He was the heart of this ensemble and when in 2008 the trio decided to separate, it was not the end for Menahem Pressler’s career – in fact it was the start of a most remarkable and successful path as a soloist and in 2013, the 90-year-old grand seigneur of the piano gave his long overdue debut with the Berliner Philharmoniker. In ‘The life I love – the pianist Menahem Pressler’, from talks with Pressler over excerpts from one of his Master Classes, to interviews with artists like Daniel Harding, Quatuor Ébène, Leonidas Kavakos or Daniel Hope, we will gain deep insights into the life of this enchantingly “venerable prodigy”. programme.desc: Tim och Fuzz tar sig till ostra London for att hamta en 1964 Porsche 356, vilket ar utan tvekan den varsta bilen de har tagit sig an. Trots alla problem under all rost, doljer sig en billegend då 356:an var bilen som gjorde Porsche till en hojdare bland dyra sportbilar.

programme.title: Hitlers sista faste
programme.desc: Mars 1945. De allierades armeer vantar langs Rhen på att invadera Nazityskland och generalerna tavlar om vems arme som forst ska ta sig over floden. Hitler har gett order om att ingen bro får falla i de allierades hander. Så nar ett tillfalle ovantat visar sig borjar en dramatisk kapplopning for att ta sig over floden och andra krigets forlopp.

programme.title: Hitlers sista faste
programme.desc: Amerikanska fallskarmsjagare landsatta I Frankrike infor Dagen D slåss mot nazistiska trupper om en viktig bro bakom fiendens linjer.

programme.title: Kingdom of the Mummies
programme.desc: Nyligen upptacktes ett gravkomplex i Saqquara dar sarskilt en gravkammare utmarkte sig. Medan de andra kamrarna var fulla med mumier, fanns dar en enda massiv stensarkofag. For dr Ramadan Hussein och hans team blir det en enorm utmaning att forsoka lyfta det fem ton tunga locket till den 2 600 år gamla stenkistan. Vilka hemligheter kan de fora fram i ljuset om agaren av den mystiska graven?

programme.title: Ice Road Rescue
programme.desc: Thord Paulsen och resten av grabbarna ser tillbaka på den senaste sasongen och funderar kring ett raddningsuppdrag som gick fruktansvart snett.

programme.title: Life Below Zero: Port Protection Alaska
programme.desc: Gary åker till Alaska och ombes ta med några ankor hem till samhallet. Timothy ger sig ut for att jaga bjornar på egen hand.

programme.title: Liberation: D-Day to Berlin
programme.desc: 6 juni 1944. Nar de allierades armeer stormar Normandies strander stalls Frankrikes befolkning infor den totala forodelse som skoljer over landet.

programme.title: Liberation: D-Day to Berlin
programme.desc: Vi tittar narmare på den verkliga kostnaden for befrielsen av Vasteuropa och skildrar kampen for att befria Belgien och Nederlanderna från nazisternas ockupation.

programme.title: Haverikommissionen
programme.desc: På vag mot Comodora vid Patagoniens kust stortdyker SOL Airlines flight 5428 plotsligt ner i en avlagsen oken. Samtliga ombord dor omedelbart. De argentinska utredarna genomsoker de branda, utspridda resterna men finner ingenting ovanligt. Åtminstone inte tills ett mikroskopiskt fiber ger en forsta konkret ledtråd.

programme.title: Haverikommissionen
programme.desc: En toppmodern helikopter som transporterar oljearbetare till en borrplattform kraschar i havet utanfor Newfoundlands kust. Otroligt nog overlever en person och inom några timmar ar ett omfattande bargningspådrag igång for att barga kropparna, den svarta lådan och vraket från havsbotten. Utredarna pusslar ihop bitarna och avslojar till slut en fatal brist i helikopterns design.

programme.title: Ice Road Rescue
programme.desc: Bjørn och Thord måste samla ett tiomannateam for att undsatta ett kapsejsat slap och dess vardefulla last. Slapet har kraschat in i ett snodike, och de två bossarna behover all sin kompetens och erfarenhet for att få tillbaka det på vagen igen. Långt upp i norr vill ungtuppen Ole Henrik visa sin far, Jo Roger, vem som bestammer under en undsattning av en avfallsbil som fastnat på ett islager.

programme.title: Ice Road Rescue
programme.desc: Thord måste slåss mot vinterns storsta snostorm for att undsatta en lastbil med enorma jarnror, och Tor Steinar riskerar frostskador for att undsatta en lastbil med slap som har frusna bromsar. Jo Roger forsoker undsatta en 35 ton tung gravskopa som glidit nerfor en brant backe, men den extrema kylan får utrustningen att fallera – och nar omtåligt stål brister hamnar liv i farozonen.

programme.title: Ice Road Rescue
programme.desc: En tankbil full med avfall glider bakåt på en smal, isig backe och krockar nastan med en snotackt bil. Det ar en svår situation som tvingar Thord att anvanda sin latta pickup – men ett enda misstag kan forvandla raddningsaktionen till en katastrof. I Overhalla stannar bargaren Marius till vid Jo Rogers verkstad på sin resa soderut. Men nar besoket avbryts av ett nodrop bjuder Jo Roger in Marius att delta i raddningsaktionen. Det som var en tio minuters kaffepaus forvandlas till en hård natts arbete.

programme.title: Mysterious Islands
programme.desc: Femtiotre manskliga kvarlevor med skottskador gravs upp på en obebodd o i Kroatien. Sex mystiska flygande foremål ses ovanfor Puget Sound. På Isle of Wight upptacker paleontologer de fossila kvarlevorna av en tidigare okand dinosaurieart. Markliga rituella artefakter upptacks i Sverige och visar på dess religiosa roll under medeltiden och antiken.

programme.title: Strangest Things
programme.desc: Tutankhamuns mask ar en av de mest ikoniska och studerade skatterna från det gamla Egypten – men markliga marken tyder på ett djupare mysterium. Årtionden senare, under andra varldskriget, upptacktes ovanliga foremål gjorda av tra, rep, sandsackar och krut utspridda over USA och Kanada. Och i London pekar en lerkruka med en bisarr blandning av manniskohår, naglar och urin på morka medeltida ritualer.

programme.title: Atlas of Cursed Places
programme.desc: Bermudatriangeln. Alla har hort talas om detta område forbannat hav utanfor USA:s ostkust, dar fartyg och flygplan forsvinner utan forklaring. Eller gor de det? Sam dyker ner i historien bakom Bermudatriangelns forbannelse och vander sig till havsforskare, fysiker och sannolikhetsanalytiker for att bokstavligen gå till botten med detta urgamla mysterium.

programme.title: Life Below Zero: Port Protection Alaska
programme.desc: Under den skoningslosa vintern måste invånarna i Port Protection utnyttja sina livskompetenser for att overleva.

programme.title: Life Below Zero: Port Protection Alaska
programme.desc: Trots de iskalla temperaturerna måste invånarna i Port Protection fortsatta att arbeta om de vill fortsatta leva sina liv på den avlagsna on.

programme.title: Beskyddare av egyptens skatter
programme.desc: Archaeologists investigate the suspicious death of Tutankhamun. Egyptologist Aliaa Ismail examines the circumstances surrounding the boy King’s demise to uncover if he was murdered. At Saqqara, experts unearth a stunning sarcophagus from the era following Tuts death. And in a necropolis at Aswan, experts make a shocking discovery that could shed light on how the young pharaoh may have died.

programme.title: Beskyddare av egyptens skatter
programme.desc: Arkeologerna undersoker hur den maktiga Nilfloden styrt alla aspekter av liv och dod i det forntida Egypten. I Aswan graver arkeologerna ut en utsmyckad, 4 000 år gammal grav langs Nilens strander. I Deir El Bahri undersoker teamet några mystiska kranier från nilkrokodiler, och experter undersoker hur Nilen forvandlade det forntida Egypten till en av antikens storsta civilisationer.

programme.title: Norges tøffeste
programme.desc: Konkurransen er nådeløs, og tiden har allerede kommet for at førstemann må dra. Den som vil være trygg må tviholde på plassen i dagens konkurranse.

programme.desc: Tystaren vil ha tak i ein av dei mest frykta gjengleiarane i Sverige for å kjøpe seg fri. Men planen er risikabel. Har han fleire utvegar?

programme.title: The King of Queens
programme.desc: When Arthur tries to sell Spence his adjoining burial plot, he somehow winds up selling it to Spences mother, Veronica. Doug is assigned a new delivery route and is freaked out by a man at one of his daily stops who always answers the door wearing nothing but a towel around his waist. Meanwhile, Carrie takes on dog walking with Holly to make some money after being unemployed for several months, but immediately hates the job and hires a kid to do the walking for her.

programme.title: The Golden Bachelor
programme.desc: Fyrrum NFL leikmaðurinn Mel Owens leitar að ástinni í hopi fongulegra kvenna.

programme.title: Dare to Be Wild
programme.desc: Dramatísk mynd frá 2015 sem er byggð á sonnum atburðum og segir frá Mary Reynolds sem korn ung að árum kom, sá og sigraði á einni bestu og virtustu bloma- og garðasýningu heims, The Chelsea flower show. Mary Reynolds var náttúrubarn í húð og hár. Hún fekk snemma áhuga á groðurræktun og garðhonnun og hafði allt aðrar hugmyndir um garða og hvernig þeir ættu að vera en flest annað folk. Þær hugmyndir gengu fyrst og fremst út á að garðar ættu að endurspegla náttúruna og náttúrulega honnun frekar en mannlega. Með þær hugmyndir barðist hún fyrir að fá að taka þátt í The Chelsea Flower Show, þar sem hún slo svo hressilega í gegn.

programme.title: No Man of God
programme.desc: Árið 1980 var raðmorðinginn bandaríski Ted Bundy dæmdur til dauða. Á árunum eftir að domurinn fell samþykkti hann að segja frá ýmsum atriðum sem tengdust glæpunum, en hann vildi aðeins tala við einn mann. Bill Hagmaier, greinandi hjá alríkislogreglunni, hitti Ted Bundy í þeirri von að fá betri skilning á því afhverju Bundy framdi hina hræðilegu glæpi, í þeirri von að fjolskyldur fornarlambanna gætu náð meiri sátt. Eftir því sem Hagmaier grefur sig dýpra inn í sjúkan huga Bundy verða til bond milli þeirra sem hvorugur átti von á að gætu orðið til. Myndin er byggð á raunverulegum handritum af samtolum þeirra Hagmaier og Bundy.

programme.title: The Glass Castle
programme.desc: Jeannette Walls fæddist árið 1960 og olst upp ásamt þremur systkinum í mikilli fátækt, oreiðu og afskiptaleysi. Faðir þeirra var drykkfelldur skýjaglopur og moðirin sagðist vera listakona þott hún skapaði aldrei neitt af viti. Fjolskyldan festi hvergi rætur, var stoðugt að flytja (flýja) og hvorki Jeannette ne systkini hennar gengu í skola á uppvaxtarárunum.

programme.title: Suburbicon
programme.desc: Þegar fækkar um einn í íbúatolu bæjarins Suburbicon eftir að glæpamenn ráðast inn á heimili Gardner-hjonanna og myrða húsmoðurina fer í gang serkennileg atburðarás sem enginn hefði getað seð fyrir. En auðvitað er ekki allt sem sýnist. Með aðalhlutverk fara Matt Damon og Julianne Moore. Leikstjori: George Clooney. Atriði í myndinni eru ekki við hæfi barna.
